text: Michaela Sokolich-Beatson (born 2 October 1996 in Auckland, New Zealand) is a New Zealand netball player. She plays for the Northern Mystics in the ANZ Premiership, having debuted in 2016.Michaela Sokolich-Beatson at Northern Mystics. Retrieved 21 July 2019. She was selected for the New Zealand national netball team, the Silver Ferns, to compete in the 2018 Commonwealth Games, where New Zealand finished fourth.Michaela Sokolich-Beatson at Silver Ferns. Retrieved 21 July 2019.Michaela Sokolich-Beatson at GC2018 Commonwealth Games. Retrieved 21 July 2019.
